data

Class Data

  • java.lang.Object
    • data.Data
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<Data>

    public class Data
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Data>
    Data is a class that is used to hold some information about a file: its size and the crc32 hash. The crc32 hash needs unsigned 32 bits to be stored, hence it is stored in a long data type.

    This class is mainly used in the main method of the class Checking.
    Some description of the use case there is described in the class ArrayListOfData.

    This object type is currently not used anywhere else in the project other the Checking class.

    • Method Detail

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Data anotherData)
        Compares 2 Data objects by comparing their file sizes and crc32 hashes.

        It first compares the "size"'s of both Data objects, if the "size"'s are found to be not equal, it would return a positive or negative number depending on the relation of the "size" of the Data object the Method was called on when compared to the "size" of the "anotherData" object passed as an argument, otherwise in case they have of equal "size"'s, it would compares the crc32 hash ("crc32") of both Data objects, if the crc32 hashes are also found to be equal, it would return 0, otherwise it subtracts the crc32 hash of "anotherData" and returns the result.

        Specified by:
        compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Data>
        Parameters:
        anotherData - the Data object to be compared against
        Returns:
        the value 0 if "anotherData" is equal to this Data object (equal "size" and crc32 hash), a value less than 0 if this Data object has smaller "size" or if they have equal "size"'s but this Data object has a smaller crc32 hash, a value greater than 0 if this Data object has greater "size" or if they have equal "size"'s but this Data object has a greater crc32 hash

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Data anotherData)
        Checks for equality between 2 Data objects by comparing their file sizes and crc32 hashes through calling the compareTo Method.

        It works basically by calling the compareTo Method and returning true only in the case where the compareTo Method returns 0 which is exactly when both Data objects are considered equal as we've explained in the documentation for compareTo. Otherwise it would return false.

        Parameters:
        anotherData - the Data object to be checked whether it is equal to this Data object
        Returns:
        true if "anotherData" is equal to this Data object (equal "size" and crc32 hash), false otherwise
